## Plan: AI Grounding, Reliability & World Tracking Overhaul

**DRAFT — Full Phased Roadmap**

This plan addresses 15 concrete improvements uncovered by the diagnostic suite + code analysis. The story.json data shows the AI produced **13 issues across 43 turns** — prose-only responses, hallucinated IDs, phantom NPCs, narrative-only items/companions, a frozen location prompt, and entirely dormant world enrichment. The fixes span from critical engine bugs to new systems (companions, NPC memory, scene facts) to activating the background AI.

---

**Steps**

### Phase 0 — Critical Engine Bugs (3 fixes) ✅ COMPLETE

These were blocking issues that undermined everything else. All three fixed, tested, and verified.

1. ✅ **Fix location ordering bug in `applyGMStateChanges()`** — Reordered `applyGMStateChanges()` into Phase A (world-building additions: `npcsAdded`, `locationsAdded`, `questsAdded`) → Phase B (validated mutations: `locationChange`, `npcChanges`, `questUpdates`, etc.). This fixed the critical "party forever at Old Warehouse" bug where the AI creates a location and moves there in the same turn but the move was silently dropped.
   - **Files changed:** `adventure-turn.ts` (lines 668-895)
   - **Tests:** `moves party to a location created in the same turn`, `modifies an NPC created in the same turn`, `updates a quest created in the same turn`

2. ✅ **Add ID validation to state change application** — Added `console.warn()` + skip for all ID references: `hpChanges[].characterId`, `conditionsApplied[].characterId`, `xpAwarded[].characterId`, `npcChanges[].npcId`, `questUpdates[].questId`, `itemsGained[].characterId`, `itemsLost[].characterId` + `itemId`, and `locationChange.to`. Invalid entries are logged and skipped instead of silently corrupting state.
   - **Files changed:** `adventure-turn.ts` (throughout Phase B blocks)
   - **Tests:** 9 validation tests covering unknown characterId, npcId, questId, itemId, and locationChange across all state change types

3. ✅ **Persist and surface scene facts** — Added `sceneFacts: string[]` to `GameState`. In `applyGMStateChanges()`, `sceneFactsAdded` entries are now appended to `state.sceneFacts` with deduplication and a 50-entry FIFO cap. In `buildSystemPrompt()`, added `=== ESTABLISHED FACTS ===` section showing the last 20 facts. Migration backfills `sceneFacts: []` for old states.
   - **Files changed:** `types.ts` (GameState interface), `adventure-turn.ts` (application logic), `gm-context.ts` (prompt section), `state.ts` (createInitialGameState + migrateV1toV2)
   - **Tests:** `accumulates sceneFactsAdded`, `deduplicates scene facts`, `applies FIFO cap at 50`, `includes scene facts in system prompt`, `does NOT include section when empty`, `shows at most last 20 facts`, `backfills sceneFacts for legacy states`, `preserves existing sceneFacts`, `createInitialGameState includes sceneFacts`

**Test count: 985 → 1006 (21 new tests, all passing)**

### Phase 1 — Prompt Grounding Overhaul (6 improvements to gm-context.ts) ✅ COMPLETE

The system prompt is the primary lever for AI reliability. These changes give the AI better situational awareness.

4. ✅ **Add `=== KNOWN NPCs (away from party) ===` section** — Shows all alive NPCs at non-current locations, grouped by location name, sorted by role priority (ally > quest-giver > merchant > neutral > hostile > boss, then by disposition desc). Capped at `MAX_KNOWN_NPCS = 25`. Each line includes NPC ID in brackets, role, and disposition label. Interaction summary from scene facts appended when relevant.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (new section in `buildSystemPrompt()`, new `dispositionLabel()` helper, new `MAX_KNOWN_NPCS` constant)
   - **Tests:** 10 tests — remote NPC grouping by location, dead NPC exclusion, local NPCs excluded from section, ID tags + disposition in current location, role-priority sorting, 25-NPC cap, section absent when no remote NPCs, disposition labels (adoring/friendly/warm/neutral/unfriendly/hostile/hateful), multi-location grouping

5. ✅ **Add `=== COMPANIONS ===` section** — After the PARTY block, shows alive NPCs with `role === 'ally'` at the party's current location. Includes stat block summary (HP/maxHP, AC, attack names with to-hit and damage) when `statBlock` is present. Intro text tells AI these NPCs participate in combat. Interaction summary from scene facts appended.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (new section in `buildSystemPrompt()`)
   - **Tests:** 7 tests — ally at party location shown, section absent when no local allies, stat block details (HP/AC/attacks), graceful rendering without stat block, dead allies excluded, non-ally roles excluded, section ordering after PARTY

6. ✅ **Add `=== KNOWN LOCATIONS ===` section** — Shows all non-current locations with `[visited]`/`[unvisited]` tags, location type in parentheses, and connection names resolved from IDs. Capped at `MAX_KNOWN_LOCATIONS = 15`. Appears between CURRENT LOCATION and KNOWN NPCs sections.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (new section in `buildSystemPrompt()`, new `MAX_KNOWN_LOCATIONS` constant)
   - **Tests:** 7 tests — visited/unvisited tags, connection name resolution, current location excluded, section absent when only one location, 15-location cap, location type shown, section ordering between CURRENT LOCATION and PARTY

7. ✅ **Show all quest statuses with tags** — Changed quest filter from `status === 'active'` to all statuses (active, available, completed, failed). Section header renamed from `=== ACTIVE QUESTS ===` to `=== QUESTS ===`. Each quest line now includes `[status]` tag.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (quest filter + header in `buildSystemPrompt()`)
   - **Tests:** 8 tests — active/available/completed/failed quests shown with tags, all statuses together, section absent when empty, objective checkboxes, section name verification

8. ✅ **Harden response format with CRITICAL RULES section** — Added `=== CRITICAL RULES ===` section after the JSON schema with 7 explicit rules: NPCs must use npcsAdded, items must use itemsGained/itemsLost, companion combat actions + npcChanges, separate creatures entries for each enemy, no instant combat (multi-turn encounters), only reference existing IDs, record facts via sceneFactsAdded. Moved `characterId` instruction to this section with reference to PARTY brackets. Updated JSON schema to use `"exact-id-from-PARTY-brackets"` placeholder.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (response format section restructured in `buildSystemPrompt()`)
   - **Tests:** 10 tests — CRITICAL RULES section exists, npcsAdded rule, itemsGained/itemsLost rule, companion combat rule, no instant encounter rule, separate creature entries rule, existing IDs only rule, sceneFactsAdded persistence rule, characterId references PARTY, schema placeholder label

9. ✅ **NPC interaction summaries via scene facts** — Added `buildNpcInteractionSummary(npc, sceneFacts)` helper that cross-references NPC name (full name + first name if ≥3 chars) against scene facts, returning the last 3 matches joined by "; ". Summary is appended to NPC lines in both KNOWN NPCs and COMPANIONS sections with " — " separator.
   - **Files changed:** `gm-context.ts` (new `buildNpcInteractionSummary()` helper, integrated into NPC listing lines)
   - **Tests:** 7 tests — facts shown in KNOWN NPCs, facts shown in COMPANIONS, first-name matching for multi-word names, 3-fact cap (checks NPC line specifically), no summary when no matching facts, short first names (<3 chars) not matched, empty sceneFacts handled gracefully

**Test count: 1006 → 1056 (50 new tests, all passing)**

### Phase 2 — Companion System (5 changes) ✅ COMPLETE

Full party-member companions that persist, fight, and travel with the party.

10. ✅ **Add `'companion'` to `NpcRole`** — Extended the union type in types.ts to include `'companion'`. Updated COMPANIONS filter in gm-context.ts from `role === 'ally'` to `role === 'ally' || role === 'companion'`. Added `'companion': 0` to npcRolePriority map (same priority as ally). Updated npcsAdded role list in response format to include `companion`.
   - **Files changed:** `types.ts` (NpcRole union), `gm-context.ts` (COMPANIONS filter, role priority, response format)
   - **Tests:** Companion NPCs shown in COMPANIONS section, both ally and companion roles shown together, companion role gets same sort priority as ally in KNOWN NPCs

11. ✅ **Add `companionPromoted` state change** — New field on `StateChange`: `companionPromoted?: { npcId: GameId; statBlock: CreatureStatBlock }`. When applied, sets the NPC's role to `'companion'`, attaches a copy of the stat block, and syncs `locationId` to `partyLocationId`. Added to `mergeStateChanges()` with engine-takes-precedence semantics. Added to response format instructions in gm-context.ts. Added companion recruitment instruction to CRITICAL RULES.
   - **Files changed:** `types.ts` (StateChange interface), `adventure-turn.ts` (applyGMStateChanges + mergeStateChanges), `gm-context.ts` (response format + CRITICAL RULES)
   - **Tests:** Promotes existing NPC to companion with stat block, moves promoted companion to party location, skips unknown npcId with console.warn, promotes NPC created via npcsAdded in same turn

12. ✅ **Auto-move companions on `locationChange`** — In `applyGMStateChanges()`, after processing `locationChange` and setting `loc.visited = true`, loops through all NPCs and updates `locationId` for alive companions (`npc.alive && npc.role === 'companion'`). Dead companions stay where they fell; non-companion NPCs (ally, merchant, etc.) are not moved.
   - **Files changed:** `adventure-turn.ts` (locationChange block in applyGMStateChanges)
   - **Tests:** Companion moves on location change, non-companion NPCs stay behind, dead companions not moved, multiple companions move simultaneously

13. ✅ **Include companions in `encounterStarted` combatants** — When `applyGMStateChanges()` processes `encounterStarted`, filters alive companion NPCs at the party location with stat blocks and maps them to `Combatant` objects (using statBlock HP/maxHP/AC/resistances/immunities/vulnerabilities). Companion combatants get `type: 'npc'`, `referenceId` matching NPC id, and `id` prefixed with `cmb-`.
   - **Files changed:** `adventure-turn.ts` (encounterStarted block in applyGMStateChanges)
   - **Tests:** Companion appears as combatant with correct stat block values, companions without stat block excluded, dead companions excluded, companions at different locations excluded

14. ✅ **Track companion HP via `npcChanges`** — Extended `npcChanges` to support `field: 'hp'`. When `nc.field === 'hp'` and the NPC has a statBlock, applies the value clamped to `[0, maxHp]`. Updated response format to show `"disposition|alive|hp"` field options. Added CRITICAL RULES instruction about using `field: "hp"` for companion HP changes.
   - **Files changed:** `adventure-turn.ts` (npcChanges block in applyGMStateChanges), `gm-context.ts` (response format + CRITICAL RULES)
   - **Tests:** HP damage applied to statBlock, HP clamped to 0 (no negatives), HP clamped to maxHp (no over-healing), HP change on NPC without statBlock has no effect, HP change combined with alive=false in same turn

